Previous Save Backup¶{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg1252\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset0 Arial;}}{&1310}{\colortbl ;\red0\green0\blue0;}{&1310}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\sl0\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\fs22 Dek:{&1310}\par \i0 For web designers, graduating is only half the battle - read up on some of the more common interview questions for your career field so you can be ahead of the marketablilty curve.  \i {&1310}\par {&1310}\par Article:\i0 {&1310}\par You may think that after battling your way through nearly a hundred web design courses, you're ready for everything - your markup clean, your CSS semantic, your (document).ready.  But the interview process is a notorious bottleneck for even the best designers.  Being able to communicate well with a computer is one thing, but being able to make a good impression on the people you’re interviewing (and will subsequently be working) with is a huge deciding factor.  Below are 25 of the most common interview questions for a web design job:{&1310}\par {&1310}\par \b Job Related{&1310}\par \b0 1.  Why are you leaving your current company?{&1310}\par 2.  If you're faced with a tough problem, how long will you spend trying to solve it before you ask someone for help?{&1310}\par 3.  Are you able to manage your own time?{&1310}\par 4.  If something urgent happens at night or over the weekend and your assistance is needed, are you able to work remotely?{&1310}\par 5.  Can you handle a fast-paced, occasionally stressful work environment?{&1310}\par 6.  Can you interact professionally with clients via email, conference call, or face to face meeting?  {&1310}\par 7.  Are you willing to take on multiple roles (i.e. designer{&47}developer)?{&1310}\par {&1310}\par \b Industry Related\b0 {&1310}\par 8.  What magazines or blogs do you follow to keep up with the industry?{&1310}\par 9.  Do you know what the w3c is, and why it’s important?{&1310}\par 10.  What emerging technologies do you think are the most important to start learning and implementing now?{&1310}\par 11.  What are some of your favorite sites?{&1310}\par 12.  What DTD are you using on current sites?{&1310}\par 13.  How much, if any, CSS3 and HTML5 should be used in web projects in order for the site to be accessable by everyone?{&1310}\par {&1310}\par {&1310}\par \b Skills Related{&1310}\par \b0 14.  On a scale of one to ten, how well do you know (any programming language)?{&1310}\par 15.  Are you experienced with working in a collaborative, team environment?{&1310}\par 16.  Can we see your portfolio?{&1310}\par 17.  Can we see samples of your code?{&1310}\par 18.  What skills{&47}languages{&47}techniques are you most interested in learning?{&1310}\par 19.  Can you fix this sample of code?{&1310}\par 20.  What tools do you use to develop?{&1310}\par {&1310}\par \b Company Related{&1310}\par \b0 21.  Why do you want this job?{&1310}\par 22.  Why do you want to work with our company?{&1310}\par 23.  With your skillset, how are you able to add immediate value to our work?{&1310}\par 24.  Where do you see yourself in five years?{&1310}\par 25.  Is there anything I haven’t told you about the company or position that you’d like to know?{&1310}\par {&1310}\par {&1310}\par \i Sources:{&1310}\par http:{&47}{&47}www.gaslampmedia.com{&47}blog{&47}11-common-web-design-company-interview-questions{&1310}\par http:{&47}{&47}www.seomoz.org{&47}blog{&47}interviewing-web-developers-20-good-questions-to-ask\i0 {&1310}\par {&1310}\par {&1310}\par }{&1310}
